text: Jacks Defeat Creek is a stream in Monroe County, Indiana, in the United States. It is a tributary of Beanblossom Creek. Jacks Defeat Creek was so named from an incident when two men, Jack Storm and Jack Ketcham were crossing the creek on horseback and both became stuck in the mud. ==See also== *List of rivers of Indiana ==References== Category:Rivers of Monroe County, Indiana Category:Rivers of Indiana
title: Jacks Defeat Creek
